cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-order formulas and their definability on sets of trees. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses regular languages of infinite binary trees. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with regular languages. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the computability of measures of languages. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with measures of sets of trees, which can be seen as a topic in discrete mathematics.
